                <pb facs="0403" n="381" xml:id="pg_381"/>
                <p rend="flushleft">I. <hi rend="italic">Peace Treaty With Italy</hi>
                </p>
                <p>1. <hi rend="italic">Report by the Commission of Investigation for the
                        rectification of the Franco-Italian frontier in the Upper Roya Valley</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Mr. Marjoribanks, U.K. Representative on the Commission of investigation
                    presented the Commission’s report (<gloss target="#t_CFM461">C.F.M. (46)</gloss>
                        56).<note n="32" xml:id="d132fn32">Dated May 11, 1946, <ref target="#pg_353"
                            >p. 353</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>After an exchange of views, the Council <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to refer
                    the question to the Deputies for consideration in the light of the observations
                    made during the discussion by the French, U.K., U.S.S.R. and U.S.
                    Delegation.</p>
                <p>2. <hi rend="italic">Report by the Committee of Economic Experts</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council heard the report presented by Mr. Gregory, Chairman of the
                    Committee.</p>
                <p>The Council noted that the Committee had made no progress in its work since the
                    report tabled on 9th May (<gloss target="#t_CFM461">C.F.M. (46)</gloss> 59)<note
                        n="33" xml:id="d132fn33">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_320">p. 320</ref>.</note> and
                    instructed the Committee to continue working on the questions on its agenda.</p>
                <p>3. <hi rend="italic">Reparation Committee</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council instructed the Reparation Committee to prepare a report for 11 a.m.
                    on 15th May.</p>
                <p>4. <hi rend="italic">Withdrawal of the Allied Forces from Italy after the
                        conclusion of the Peace Treaties</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The United States and U.K. Delegations pointed out that this question was
                    connected with the problem of maintenance of the lines of communication with the
                    allied zones of occupation in Austria.</p>
                <p>The Soviet Delegation pointed out that at the first session of the Council no
                    provision had been made for the retention of allied forces in Italy after the
                    conclusion of the Peace Treaty.</p>
                <p>The Council instructed the Committee of Military Experts to study this
                    question.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">II. <hi rend="italic">Records of Previous Meeting</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council approved the records of the 10th, 11th, 12th and 13th meetings.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">III. <hi rend="italic">Next Meeting of the Council</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Council <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to meet at 4 p.m. to continue its
                    discussion of the various Draft Treaties.</p>
